description: From Middle French inutile, from Middle French, from Latin inutilis. See in- (“not”), utile.

adjectives.description: inutile (comparative more inutile, superlative most inutile)

examples: The undermediators are not required, have nothing properly to do, no peculiar duty to perform; but are an unprofitable or inutile set of beings sitting down and looking at each other through want of other occupation.
